content.description: Start sitting, with a low left juggy sidepull and a low right sidepull on the arête around the same level.  Climb the arête.
content.location: Ten minutes up from Tunder Tighs and barely left.  Just below and next to the One Word Boulder.

content.description: From the start of Rogue (a three finger edge for the right, and a pinch just next to it for the left) climb the center of the over hanging face, likely pinching arete features.  This will be good and quite hard.

Start with a three finger edge for the right hand and a very obvious pinch/ slopey crimp next to it.  Bust left to another pinch and continue leftwards, gaining a jug and a crimpy bulge/slab encounter.
content.location: On the One Word Boulder, starting in the center of the face. A ten minute walk above Tunder Tighs and slightly left.

content.description: From a right undercling and left sidepull, bust a long move up the arête feature to a gaston.  Tricky moves lead to an easing finish.
content.protection: Several pads, though maybe a couple could do it.
content.location: On the One Word Boulder.  A ten minute hike up and just barely left from the Tunder Tighs Boulder.

content.description: The far right line on the One Word Boulder.  Start right hand above your head on a two finger crimp and left lower on a pinch or undercling hold with a good ledge for the feet.  Climb up.  A lower start is undone.
content.location: 10 minutes above tunder tighs and slightly left.

content.description: Stand start with a thin crimp at the 6 foot level left of the arête and a low, thin undercling right of the arête.  With difficulty, pull on, gain the lip then head up and right to finish.
content.location: On the north side of the Vanilla Ice Boulder which is just below and next to the One Word Boulder.

content.description: Situated in a very narrow open boulder field.
